cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "1-Bit Recursive Sudoku Solver: BitDistill on Tiny Recursive Models"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Barrett
    given-names: Richard
    affiliation: Independent researcher
repository-code: "https://github.com/RNBBarrett/1-Bit-TRM-Sudoku-Solver"
url: "https://github.com/RNBBarrett/1-Bit-TRM-Sudoku-Solver"
abstract: >-
  First 1-bit (BitNet b1.58 ternary weight) recursive reasoner for the
  Sudoku-Extreme benchmark. The 7M-parameter Tiny Recursive Model (TRM)
  architecture from Samsung SAIL Montreal is quantized to ternary weights
  via knowledge distillation from a full-precision teacher. Direct
  quantization-aware-training-from-scratch fails for recursive
  architectures; KD with the v6 BitNet stabilization recipe (lambda
  warmup, learnable per-layer alpha, median weight scaling, EMA at 0.999)
  rescues it. Result: a ~1.4 MB ternary-weight Sudoku reasoner suitable
  for microcontroller-class deployment.
keywords:
